product.name: Samsung Galaxy Book Go Laptop PC Computer Qualcomm 7C Pro 4GB Memory 128GB eUFS Storage 18-Hour Battery Compact Light Shockproof WFH Ready WiFi 5, Silver

top_positive_review.date: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2021
top_positive_review.title: Student Laptop
top_positive_review.review: As a graduate student this laptop is perfect. It’s Affordable and the battery life is better than most expensive PCs out there.

top_critical_review.date: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2021
top_critical_review.title: Possible design flaw
top_critical_review.review: I love the idea behind Book Go but be aware of flaws.1. This unit shouldn’t be Windows 11 compatible. Every OS is getting power hungry and bare minimum spec won’t do you any good. 4GB ram and 128GB hard drive will hinder your unit almost useless. It may be able to do at most dual-task not multitask.2. Design is nice and clean but visible flaw on the screen. When you open the unit and lay flat on a table, you will notice a ripple of wave visible on the bottom corners of the screen whenever any slight pressure is applied to the corner of the unit. That includes your palms touching the palm ray area when typing, gently moving the angle of the screen by nudging the top of the screen slightly.3.  60% of 128GB are already reserved for operating, which means only 50GB of usable memories after installing OS 11, no other apps added. (20GB of temp file as previous OS as backup)

reviews.title: Best laptop under 500 dollars, by far
reviews.review: The most modern design, light, a ridiculous 18 hours of battery life (I haven't tested this yet), and a feel-good keyboard to use.

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2021
reviews.title: SAMSUNG  Galaxy Book Go
reviews.review: it is a good item based on the selling price but cannot install the antivirus software due to the CPU not Intel or AMD.

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2021
reviews.title: So far, so good
reviews.review: I've only received my Galaxy Book Go today and I've been setting everything up and trying it out. All the Samsung services I use like Quick Share work great, Samsung Notes synced well and Your Phone works well. Build quality is so-so, being plastic and all, it does have a little bit of give near the top of the keyboard. It is lightweight and that's a plus for me. Screen is a little washed out and doesn't have the best viewing angles, but all of this is passable considering the $300 price. My much older laptop was all plastic too but weighed almost twice as much. The keyboard has pretty good travel and I can type with ease. Sound is good, too. I'm new to Windows on ARM, but this reminds me more of a Chromebook than an actual Windows device with Intel o AMD processors. It is fast to start up and I feel, for my needs and use, this will be a great device. I'll try it out more with fingers crossed so as not to run into any serious issues.

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2021
reviews.title: Fastest delivery I’ve ever received
reviews.review: I ordered this computer yesterday and it was delivered to my house this morning! It actually came before I had to log on to my 9am zoom class with enough time for me to charge it, set it up, download zoom and sync with my printer(seriously all in under 15 minutes)!The computer itself is great for what I need: something that will get me through my graduate studies. For the price, the computer can’t be beat. I was initially considering a chrome book because I was just looking for an inexpensive computer, but I like the idea that I will still be able to use it in the event that we lose power/internet (which is a common concern in the winter) because it’s Microsoft office enabled so I can still complete my work. It’s light and sleek, though I may not want to test it’s “shockproof” feature. I’ve had two MacBooks in the past 7 years and I’ve been disappointed with their longevity(especially because of their cost), so I figured I’d buy something that is a little more financially responsible to replace, and I’m happy with my purchase!

reviews.title: Keyboard
reviews.review: I disliked the fact that the wasn't a seperate number key pad and that it was a touch screen. At my age I was in need of the easy way with a mouse. I tried to make it work because of the name Samsung and also the price. I am shopping for a larger laptop with full keyboard.

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2021
reviews.title: This a very good device for the money.
reviews.review: You must remember that nothing, and that is nothing, is made anymore in the US.  Everything is made in Asia, Korea, China, Bangladesh, Vietnam nowadays.  If there was a war with China, despite all the destruction, there would be nothing in WalMart.  This is a Korean PC and it works well.

reviews.title: Great Computer
reviews.review: Great computer for the price!  Good quality and fast processor. Never gets hot, so I can work with it on my lap for as long as I want.I would highly recommend it if you are looking for a low price and quality for the price.
